text: Posted by Defense World Staff on Mar 24th, 2024 Sterling Investment Counsel LLC increased its holdings in  Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOGL – Free Report) by 1.8% in the fourth quarter, according to the company in its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission. The firm owned 31,785 shares of the information services provider’s stock after purchasing an additional 572 shares during the period. Alphabet accounts for  2.3% of Sterling Investment Counsel LLC’s investment portfolio, making the stock its 9th biggest position. Sterling Investment Counsel LLC’s holdings in Alphabet were worth $4,440,000 as of its most recent SEC filing.
